---
import BlogPost from '../../../../layouts/BlogPost.astro';

export const frontmatter = {
	title: "The Apple Melaka Airbnb Investment 2026 | 7-9% ROI Review | 700+ Properties",
	description: "Is The Apple Melaka good for Airbnb investment? Real 2026 data: 7-9% ROI, RM280+ nightly rates, 65-75% occupancy. How it compares to Atlantis & Silverscape. 700+ properties managed since 2017.",
	date: "2026-03-24",
	category: "property-review",
	image: "/images/blog/the-apple-melaka-airbnb-review-2026.jpg",
	author: "iHousing Team"
};

const faqSchema = {
	"@context": "https://schema.org",
	"@type": "FAQPage",
	"mainEntity": [
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "Is The Apple Melaka a good Airbnb investment in 2026?",
			"acceptedAnswer": {
				"@type": "Answer",
				"text": "Yes, The Apple Melaka yields 7-9% ROI for Airbnb in 2026. It commands premium rates (RM280-350/night) and attracts couples/business travelers. Lower occupancy (65-75%) than Atlantis, but higher nightly rates and lower maintenance costs due to adult guests."
			}
		},
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "How much can I earn from Airbnb at The Apple Melaka?",
			"acceptedAnswer": {
				"@type": "Answer",
				"text": "A 2-bedroom unit at The Apple Melaka earns RM5,500-7,000/month gross revenue. After cleaning, utilities (~RM1,200), and management fees (~RM350), net operating income is RM4,000-5,450/month. Cash-flow positive if mortgage is under RM3,500."
			}
		},
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "What is the difference between The Apple and Atlantis Melaka for Airbnb?",
			"acceptedAnswer": {
				"@type": "Answer",
				"text": "The Apple targets couples/business travelers with RM280-350 rates and 65-75% occupancy. Atlantis targets families with RM200-250 rates and 75-85% occupancy. The Apple has lower wear-and-tear (adult guests) but higher entry cost. Atlantis has higher volume but more maintenance."
			}
		},
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "Is Airbnb allowed at The Apple Melaka in 2026?",
			"acceptedAnswer": {
				"@type": "Answer",
				"text": "Yes, The Apple Melaka remains Airbnb-friendly in 2026 with Commercial Strata Title. Follow management rules and maintain professional standards. The hotel-grade management keeps common areas pristine—important for guest reviews."
			}
		},
		{
			"@type": "Question",
			"name": "What type of guests book The Apple Melaka on Airbnb?",
			"acceptedAnswer": {
				"@type": "Answer",
				"text": "The Apple attracts couples, business travelers, and luxury tourists—not large families. The lack of a kids' water park and premium positioning means fewer noisy groups. For owners, this means less furniture damage and longer-lasting furnishings."
			}
		}
	]
};
---

<BlogPost {...frontmatter}>
	<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
	
	<div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-8">
		<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-2">The Apple Melaka Airbnb Investment 2026: Premium Property, Premium Returns</h2>
		<p class="text-blue-700"><strong>The Verdict:</strong> The Apple Melaka is the top choice for <strong>premium travelers and couples</strong> who value location over "kid amenities." While Atlantis wins on family volume, The Apple commands higher nightly rates (RM280+) and attracts better-behaved guests. In 2026, it's yielding a solid <strong>7-9% ROI</strong> for our owners. iHousing manages <strong>700+ properties since 2017</strong>—here's our honest analysis.</p>
	</div>

	<p>If you've driven through Melaka recently, you can't miss <strong>The Apple</strong>. Sitting tall next to the Courtyard by Marriott on Jalan Tun Sri Lanang, it looks more like a luxury hotel than a typical condo. And that's exactly why it's interesting for Airbnb investors.</p>

	<p>At iHousing, we manage units across all major Melaka residences—Atlantis, Silverscape, The Wave, and The Apple. We see the real booking data every day. Here is our honest, numbers-backed review of The Apple as an investment property in 2026.</p>

	<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Location: The Real Selling Point</h2>
	<p>This is where The Apple shines. Unlike Atlantis (which requires a Grab to get anywhere) or Silverscape (which is further south), The Apple is genuinely central.</p>
	
	<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 space-y-2">
		<li><strong>The Shore Shopping Gallery:</strong> 5-minute walk.</li>
		<li><strong>Melaka River Cruise:</strong> 5-minute walk.</li>
		<li><strong>Jonker Street:</strong> 10-15 minute walk (or a cheap RM5 Grab).</li>
		<li><strong>Bunga Raya Food Street:</strong> Right nearby for authentic local food.</li>
	</ul>

	<p><strong>Why this matters for Airbnb:</strong> Guests staying here often don't need a car. This makes it a magnet for Singaporean couples who take the bus up, or international tourists who want to explore on foot.</p>

	<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">The Apple vs. The Rest (2026 Data)</h2>

